      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "unto strangers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that were among them, and in their power, which was Ben-hadad’s case; for God had delivered him into Ahab’s hand for his blasphemy, as he promised to do, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " 1 Kings 20:28",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 20:28",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", by which act of his providence, especially compared with that law, it was most evident that this man was appointed by God to destruction, as is here said. But Ahab was so far from punishing this blasphemer, that he doth not so much as rebuke him, but treats him like a friend and a brother; dismisseth him upon easy terms, and takes his word for the performance, and takes not the least care for the reparation of God’s honour, but only for the amplification of his own power. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
